ver01/data/sn90051068/00513680831/1907110901/0228.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:cohi:batch_cohi_ironton_ver01:data:sn90051068:00513680831:1907110901:0224/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/cohi/batch_cohi_ironton_ver01/data/sn90051068/00513680831/1907110901/0228.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn90051068/1907-11-09/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/cohi/batch_cohi_ironton_ver01/data/sn90051068/00513680831/1907110901/0228.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn90051068/1907-11-09/ed-1/?sp=5"], "batch": ["cohi_ironton_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/colorado/", "2/united states/colorado/rio grande/", "3/united states/colorado/rio grande/monte vista/"], "contributor": ["history colorado"], "date": "1907-11-09", "dates": ["1907-11-09"], "description": ["Nellie Duvic went to Denver Tlursday night he gold cemps are paying the miers in currency 1 The Santa Fe railroad bas been oconvicted of rebating and fined 330000 George Carpenter has been in town during the week talking life insurance Mrs O W Bylvester is doing nicely at Denver and expects to be home in week or so London has put up the price of gold in order to stop any more ex ports to the United States Sam Sibbett and wife are plan ning to go to New Mexico mn a week or 80 to spend the winter The labor nnions have decided to accept cashiers certificates in payment of wages This will go a long way to tide over the money famine R B Sheffler a real estate man from Assumption Illinois arrived m town Friday morning looking for bargains for eastern customers P Ors Maddox is in a fairway to recovery at Colorado Springs Duriog the past week her temper ature has been kept down to about 102 H H Winchell retorned Fn day morning from a business trip to Denver and Cripple Creek The panic has not hurt gold min ing so far Some twelve"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-12-27T20:56:03.507Z", "group": ["ndnp/cohi", "history-colorado-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn90051068/1907-11-09/ed-1/?sp=5", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:cohi:batch_cohi_ironton_ver01:data:sn90051068:00513680831:1907110901:0228/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=317&w=208", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:cohi:batch_cohi_ironton_ver01:data:sn90051068:00513680831:1907110901:0228/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=634&w=417", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/cohi/batch_cohi_ironton_ver01/data/sn90051068/00513680831/1907110901/0228.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["rio grande", "colorado", "united states", "monte vista"], "location_city": ["monte vista"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["rio grande"], "location_state": ["colorado"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["0000000005", "sn90051068", "3", "0", "6", "8", "1", "5"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn90051068"], "number_page": ["0000000005"], "number_reel": ["0", "0", "5", "1", "3", "6", "8", "0", "8", "3", "1"], "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Stampede edition"], "partof": ["chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "the monte vista journal (monte vista, rio grande county, colo.) 1888-1921"], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["the monte vista journal (monte vista, rio grande county, colo.) 1888-1921"], "publication_frequenc